Step-by-Step Guide:
Step 1: Design Class Structure
• Plan the attributes and methods for each class
• Define relationships between classes
• Create UML diagram or class structure sketch
Step 2: Implement Book Class
• Create Book class with __init__ method
• Add attributes: title, author, isbn, year, available (boolean)
• Add __str__ method for readable representation
• Add methods: check_out(), return_book()
Step 3: Implement Member Class
• Create Member class with __init__ method
• Add attributes: name, member_id, borrowed_books (list)
• Add methods: borrow_book(), return_book()
• Add maximum borrow limit (e.g., 5 books)
Step 4: Implement Library Class
• Create Library class to manage collections
• Add attributes: books (dictionary), members (dictionary)
• Add methods: add_book(), remove_book(), find_book()
• Add methods: register_member(), find_member()
Step 5: Implement Core Functionality
• Add borrow_book() method in Library class
• Add return_book() method with overdue calculation
• Implement search by title, author, or ISBN
• Add statistics: total books, available books, etc.
Step 6: Add File Operations
• Save/load books to JSON file
• Save/load members to JSON file
• Implement backup functionality
• Handle file errors gracefully
Step 7: Create User Interface
• Build a menu system for librarians
• Add input validation for all operations
• Create formatted displays for books and members
• Add search results display
